						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1476, Pramādi, Śrāvaṇa, ba. 5</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1553 July 29, Saturday</hi> (not verifiable), in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Sadāśivadēva-Mahārāya.</hi> It records that <hi rend="bold">Vīraṇṇa-Voḍeya's</hi> pupil (name lost) made a gift of gold for the service of the god Sōmēśvaradēva in the village of <hi rend="bold">Kaṁchisamudra</hi> surnamed <hi rend="bold">Pratāpadēvarāyapura.</hi></p>						

